    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Employee Satisfaction in Wheels India Limited, Chennai</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Venkatesh.J</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Wheels India Limited</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2010 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P4638</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">As part of my curriculum, I was deployed to study the satisfaction level of employees in Wheels India Limited, Padi, Chennai from 15 March 2010 to 07 May 2010.
The study is to find out the level of satisfaction among the supervisor and managerial category of employees of Wheels India pertaining to all the aspects of work environment. The study is focused on finding out the driving and restraining factors of employee satisfaction
The objective of this study is achieved in finding the satisfaction level and employees’ opinion towards the management.
The primary data were collected trough a structured questionnaire and the secondary data from journals, web pages and books.
The tools used for analysis and interpretation are percentage analysis, weighted average ranking method, Non-parametric tests – Chi-square test to identify the significant difference between two variables and Likert Scaling is used to derive the Employee Satisfaction Index.
The Population size used for this study is 315, which covers employees from supervisors to senior level Managers (grades: S08 to S16)
The research work gave me an exposure to study the importance of employee satisfaction in an organization and also to find out the opinion of the employees towards the management.
This exercise also gave me an opportunity to identify the areas of improvement.
The suggestions were made from the analysis and findings of the study and submitted to the Management for further considerations.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8203">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8203</a></td></tr>
